To install Sanskrit Computational Linguistics tools

a) tar -xvzf scl.tgz 

b) cp appropriate SPEC/spec*.txt file to scl directory. Name it as spec.txt
   Check that the paths are correct, else make necessary changes.

   **** Installation steps for non-SERVER version ***

c) ./configure

d) make all

e) sudo make install


   **** Installation steps for SERVER version ****

c) ./configure_server

d) make server

e) sudo make install_server


All the packages are licensed under GPL. You would have received a copy of GPL license with this package.

In case of any queries, please contact ambapradeep@gmail.com.

